---
// Static SVG diagram for AlphaFold2's recycling loop.
// Written as a .astro component rather than inline JSX in MDX so that SVG
// attributes (text-anchor, stroke-width, marker-end, etc.) are preserved
// as kebab-case, and so that <text> content isn't wrapped in <p> by MDX.
---
<figure class="recycle-fig">
  <svg
    viewBox="0 0 760 240"
    role="img"
    aria-label="AlphaFold2 recycling loop diagram"
  >
    <defs>
      <marker id="rec-arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto">
        <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="var(--fg-muted)" />
      </marker>
      <marker id="rec-arrow-accent" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="7" markerHeight="7" orient="auto">
        <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="var(--accent)" />
      </marker>
    </defs>

    {/* Row of blocks: Input features → Input embedder → Evoformer × 48 → Structure module → Predicted structure */}
    {/* y centered around 100; box height 48 */}
    <g class="rec-box rec-box--neutral">
      <rect x="20" y="76" width="120" height="48" rx="5" />
      <text x="80" y="103" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle">Input features</text>
    </g>

    <text x="160" y="100" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle" class="rec-plus">+</text>

    <g class="rec-box rec-box--neutral">
      <rect x="180" y="76" width="130" height="48" rx="5" />
      <text x="245" y="103" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle">Input embedder</text>
    </g>

    <g class="rec-box rec-box--accent">
      <rect x="330" y="76" width="120" height="48" rx="5" />
      <text x="390" y="103" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle">Evoformer × 48</text>
    </g>

    <g class="rec-box rec-box--accent">
      <rect x="470" y="76" width="140" height="48" rx="5" />
      <text x="540" y="103" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle">Structure module</text>
    </g>

    <g class="rec-box rec-box--neutral">
      <rect x="630" y="76" width="110" height="48" rx="5" />
      <text x="685" y="96" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle">Predicted</text>
      <text x="685" y="112" text-anchor="middle" dominant-baseline="middle">structure</text>
    </g>

    {/* Forward arrows (y = 100, the vertical center of each box at y 76 + 24) */}
    <g class="rec-arrow-fwd">
      <line x1="140" y1="100" x2="155" y2="100" marker-end="url(#rec-arrow)" />
      <line x1="310" y1="100" x2="325" y2="100" marker-end="url(#rec-arrow)" />
      <line x1="450" y1="100" x2="465" y2="100" marker-end="url(#rec-arrow)" />
      <line x1="610" y1="100" x2="625" y2="100" marker-end="url(#rec-arrow)" />
    </g>

    {/* Feedback loop: from right edge of Predicted box down and around to top of Input features */}
    <path
      class="rec-loop"
      d="M 685 124 L 685 180 L 80 180 L 80 124"
      marker-end="url(#rec-arrow-accent)"
    />

    <text x="385" y="204" text-anchor="middle" class="rec-loop-label">
      detach → recycle (up to 4 cycles; gradients flow only through the last)
    </text>

    {/* What is fed back — labeled with a leader line */}
    <text x="685" y="52" text-anchor="middle" class="rec-feedback-label">
      feed back: m̂₁ᵢ, ẑᵢⱼ, pseudo-β coordinates
    </text>
    <line x1="685" y1="60" x2="685" y2="72" class="rec-leader" />
  </svg>

  <figcaption>
    The recycling loop. On every cycle past the first, the MSA first row, the pair representation,
    and the pseudo-β coordinates from the previous cycle are fed back and added into the inputs —
    after LayerNorm and, for coordinates, distance binning. Gradients flow only through the last
    cycle.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .recycle-fig {
    margin: 1.75rem 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem 0.9rem;
    background: color-mix(in oklab, var(--bg) 94%, var(--rule) 6%);
  }
  .recycle-fig svg {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  /* Boxes */
  .rec-box rect { fill: color-mix(in oklab, var(--rule) 30%, transparent); stroke: var(--rule); stroke-width: 1; }
  .rec-box--accent rect { fill: color-mix(in oklab, var(--accent) 14%, transparent); stroke: var(--accent); }
  .rec-box text { fill: var(--fg); font-size: 12.5px; }

  /* The "+" between input features and the embedder */
  .rec-plus { fill: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 18px; font-weight: 500; }

  /* Forward arrows */
  .rec-arrow-fwd line { stroke: var(--fg-muted); stroke-width: 1.4; fill: none; }

  /* Feedback loop */
  .rec-loop {
    stroke: var(--accent);
    stroke-width: 1.4;
    fill: none;
    stroke-dasharray: 6 4;
  }

  /* Captions inside the SVG */
  .rec-loop-label { fill: var(--accent); font-size: 11.5px; font-style: italic; }
  .rec-feedback-label { fill: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 11px; }
  .rec-leader { stroke: var(--fg-muted); stroke-width: 0.8; stroke-dasharray: 2 2; }

  .recycle-fig figcaption {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
</style>
